Feature: GitHub API Automation Tests Scenarios
  
Background:  
  * url 'https://api.github.com'  
  * headers { Accept: 'application/vnd.github+json', Authorization: 'Bearer <YOUR-TOKEN>', 'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28' }  
  
Scenario: Get user information  
  Given path 'user'  
  When method GET  
  Then status 200  
  
Scenario: No Token Provided  
  Given path 'user'  
  And headers { Accept: 'application/vnd.github+json', 'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28' }  
  When method GET  
  Then status 401  
  
Scenario: Invalid Token Provided  
  Given path 'user'  
  And headers { Accept: 'application/vnd.github+json', Authorization: 'Bearer InvalidToken', 'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28' }  
  When method GET  
  Then status 401  
  
Scenario: Forbidden Access (Token Without Necessary Permissions)  
  Given path 'user'  
  And headers { Accept: 'application/vnd.github+json', Authorization: 'Bearer <YOUR-INVALID-TOKEN>', 'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28' }  # Replace <YOUR-INVALID-TOKEN> with a token without necessary permissions  
  When method GET  
  Then status 403  

Scenario: Get User With Valid Token  
  Given path 'user'  
  When method GET  
  Then status 200  
  
Scenario: Update User Bio With Valid Token  
  Given path 'user'  
  And request { bio: 'Your new bio content here.' }  
  When method PATCH  
  Then status 200  
